    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "As far as i recall, you can write \r\n```C\r\n#define SIZE_OF_INT sizeof(int)\r\n```\r\nin C.\r\n\r\nHowever, when I write \r\n```cython\r\nDEF USE_LONG = 1\r\nIF USE_LONG == 1:\r\n    ctypedef long Int\r\nELSE:\r\n    ctypedef int Int\r\nDEF SIZE_INT = sizeof(Int)\r\n```\r\nin Cython, the compiler gives the error: `Invalid compile-time expression` for the last line above. But the result of `sizeof(int)` can be known at compile-time.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2018-07-07T01:10:46Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This can't be done, because the generated `c` file may be compiled on platforms with different integer sizes. (There are two compile phases, `pyx` -> `c` and `c` -> `so`/`dll` and this error refers to the former whereas `sizeof(int)` is only known at the latter.)",
            "created_at": "2018-07-07T01:10:46Z",
